Tongue atrophy in mixed connective tissue disease.
 A case is reported of tongue atrophy in a patient with mixed connective tissue disease (MCTD) and major myositic involvement.
 The case highlights oropharyngeal aspects of MCTD, including inability to wear dentures, dysarthria, and dysphagia.
 To our knowledge this is the first report of major tongue involvement in myositis as part of MCTD.
